# 🌍 Global Response Handling (ResponseBodyAdvice)

---

## 📌 Concept

Global Response Handling ensures that **all API responses follow a common structure**.

Instead of returning raw data:
{
"name": "Vipul"
}

We return:
{
"status": "success",
"message": "Request successful",
"data": { "name": "Vipul" }
}

👉 Achieved using `ResponseBodyAdvice`

---

## ⚙️ Approach

### Step 1: Create ApiResponse Wrapper

```java
public class ApiResponse<T> {

    private String status;
    private String message;
    private T data;

    public ApiResponse(String status, String message, T data) {
        this.status = status;
        this.message = message;
        this.data = data;
    }
}
```

---

### Step 2: Implement ResponseBodyAdvice

```java
@RestControllerAdvice
public class GlobalResponseHandler implements ResponseBodyAdvice<Object> {
```

---

## ⚙️ Core Methods

---

### 1️⃣ supports()

#### Concept

Determines whether global response handling should be applied.

#### Code

```java
@Override
public boolean supports(MethodParameter returnType,
                        Class<? extends HttpMessageConverter<?>> converterType) {
    return true;
}
```

#### Understanding

* return true → apply to all responses
* return false → skip

#### Parameters

* MethodParameter returnType → info about controller method
* converterType → type of response converter (JSON, String, etc.)

---

### 2️⃣ beforeBodyWrite()

#### Concept

Modifies the response body before sending to client.

#### Code

```java
@Override
public Object beforeBodyWrite(
        Object body,
        MethodParameter returnType,
        MediaType contentType,
        Class<? extends HttpMessageConverter<?>> converterType,
        ServerHttpRequest request,
        ServerHttpResponse response) {

    return new ApiResponse<>("success", "Request successful", body);
}
```

#### Parameters

* body → actual response from controller ⭐
* returnType → controller method details
* contentType → response format (JSON/text)
* converterType → message converter
* request → HTTP request info
* response → HTTP response control

---

## ⚠️ Important Cases

### Avoid Double Wrapping

```java
if (body instanceof ApiResponse) {
    return body;
}
```

---

### Handle String Response

```java
if (body instanceof String) {
    return "{\"status\":\"success\",\"message\":\"OK\",\"data\":\"" + body + "\"}";
}
```

---

## 💻 Final Implementation

```java
@RestControllerAdvice
public class GlobalResponseHandler implements ResponseBodyAdvice<Object> {

    @Override
    public boolean supports(MethodParameter returnType,
                            Class<? extends HttpMessageConverter<?>> converterType) {
        return true;
    }

    @Override
    public Object beforeBodyWrite(
            Object body,
            MethodParameter returnType,
            MediaType contentType,
            Class<? extends HttpMessageConverter<?>> converterType,
            ServerHttpRequest request,
            ServerHttpResponse response) {

        if (body instanceof ApiResponse) {
            return body;
        }

        return new ApiResponse<>("success", "OK", body);
    }
}
```

---

## 🔑 Key Points

* ResponseBodyAdvice → intercepts all responses
* supports() → decides apply or not
* beforeBodyWrite() → modifies response
* body = actual controller output ⭐
* Use ApiResponse<T> for consistency
* Avoid double wrapping

---

## 🧠 Learnings

* Provides consistent API response format
* Reduces boilerplate in controllers
* Used in production-level Spring Boot apps
* Works with @RestControllerAdvice

